comment: Towns (MIN) maintains legal guarding position and Pachulia (DAL) loses control of the ball.

After communicating with the Replay Center, there was conclusive video evidence that showed that Pachulia (DAL) was the last player to touch the ball prior to it going OOB. The ruling on the court was overturned and Minnesota was awarded possession.
Rubio (MIN) sets the screen on Pachulia (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Towns (MIN) maintains legal guarding position as he contests Matthews' (DAL) driving layup attempt.
Pachulia (DAL) sets the screen on Wiggins (MIN) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Towns (MIN) sets the screen on Matthews (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Pachulia (DAL) and Williams (DAL) maintain legal guarding position and cleanly strip the ball from Wiggins (MIN). The incidental foot to foot contact occurs after the ball is knocked loose.
Towns (MIN) and Pachulia (DAL) briefly engage and separate suring rebounding.
[Incidental or immaterial] Rubio (MIN) attempts to call a time-out but the request is not acknowledged by officials because he is not seen until time expires.
Williams (DAL) makes incidental contact with Muhammad (MIN) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Rubio (MIN) does not go through the space of Matthews (DAL) as the two players make incidental contact with one another.
Pachulia (DAL) obtains a legal guarding position and jumps vertically as he contests Muhammad's (MIN) driving layup attempt.
RHH shows that Prince (MIN) and Towns (MIN) maintain legal guarding position and that Pachulia (DAL) loses the ball as he attempts to make his post move.
Parsons (DAL) obtains a legal guarding position and is firming up as he absorbs the contact from Wiggins (MIN).
[Incidental or immaterial] Pachulia (DAL) makes incidental contact with Towns (MIN) that does not affect his ability to defend.
Towns (MIN) jumps from point A to point B and makes body to body contact with Parsons (DAL) that affects his shot attempt.
Prince (MIN) makes contact with Harris' (DAL) body on his layup attempt.
Matthews (DAL) makes contact with Wiggins' (MIN) body that affects his drive to the basket.
Towns (MIN) commits a take foul on Pachulia (DAL).
Correctly called 24 second violation.
